          <p>The cell is the basic unit of life. Key components include:</p>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Nucleus:</strong> Contains DNA and controls cell activities.</li>
            <li><strong>Mitochondria:</strong> Produces ATP, the energy currency.</li>
            <li><strong>Ribosomes:</strong> Site of protein synthesis.</li>
            <li><strong>Cell Membrane:</strong> Regulates entry and exit of substances.</li>
          </ul>
